.TH "dc_stream_get_crc" 9 "dc_stream_get_crc" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
dc_stream_get_crc \- Get CRC values for the given stream.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "bool" dc_stream_get_crc
.BI "(struct dc *dc "  ","
.BI "struct dc_stream_state *stream "  ","
.BI "uint32_t *r_cr "  ","
.BI "uint32_t *g_y "  ","
.BI "uint32_t *b_cb "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dc" 12
DC object
.IP "stream" 12
The DC stream state of the stream to get CRCs from.
.IP "r_cr" 12
CRC value for the first of the 3 channels stored here.
.IP "g_y" 12
CRC value for the second of the 3 channels stored here.
.IP "b_cb" 12
CRC value for the third of the 3 channels stored here.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
dc_stream_configure_crc needs to be called beforehand to enable CRCs.
Return false if stream is not found, or if CRCs are not enabled.
